vibe: 2.0

meta:
  name: vibe_v2_migration
  description: >
    File-by-file migration strategy for the VIBE v2 pivot. Categorizes
    every file in the repository as DELETE, REWRITE, ADAPT, or KEEP,
    with rationale and target state for each.
  session_id: 2026-03-10-a7f3b2
  created_at: "2026-03-10"
  author: claude
  tags:
    - migration
    - inventory
    - v2
  status: draft

imports:
  - plans/10_format_spec.vibe
  - plans/30_stdlib_refactor.vibe

context:
  problem: |
    The v2 pivot touches nearly every file in the repository. A clear
    migration strategy prevents accidental loss of valuable content,
    ensures nothing is forgotten, and provides a work queue for
    executing the migration.

  constraints: |
    - Every file in the repository must be categorized
    - Deletions must be justified (no silent removal)
    - Rewrites must specify the target state
    - Must be executable as a checklist
    - Git history preserves v1 state (no need for backup copies)

  assumptions: |
    - Migration is executed in a single branch (not incremental)
    - Git history is sufficient for rollback
    - New spec documents are created as part of the rewrite phase
    - The MCP server is a new addition (not a migration)

  scope: |
    Covers the existing repository files only. New files (MCP server,
    new spec documents) are planned in their respective .vibe files.

sections:
  - id: files_to_delete
    type: checklist
    title: "Files to DELETE (7 files)"
    content: |
      These files exist solely to support v1 runtime execution and have
      no equivalent in v2. Content is preserved in git history.

      - [ ] vibe/stdlib/tools.vibe
            Reason: Tool definitions are an execution concern.
            Contains: fs.read, fs.write, fs.list, fs.apply_patch, exec.run schemas.
            Replacement: None. Execution tools define their own capabilities.

      - [ ] vibe/stdlib/plan_manifest_schema.vibe
            Reason: Plan manifests are a v1 execution artifact.
            Contains: Schema wiring for plan_manifest.schema.json.
            Replacement: None. No plan manifests in v2.

      - [ ] vibe/spec/VIBE_RUNTIME_CONTRACT.md
            Reason: Runtime execution contract is no longer relevant.
            Contains: Required runtime behaviors for parsing, merging,
            plan/apply, tool-truth, gates, retries, evidence, security.
            Replacement: VIBE_CONSUMER_CONTRACT.md (what consumers of .vibe
            files must understand, without execution semantics).

      - [ ] vibe/spec/VIBE_PROGRAM_IR.md
            Reason: Program IR was the compiled/merged runtime representation.
            Contains: Canonical merged representation rules.
            Replacement: VIBE_MERGE_SEMANTICS.md (simplified merge rules).

      - [ ] vibe/spec/VIBE_STEP_TYPES.md
            Reason: Step types are v1 workflow execution concepts.
            Contains: plan, generate, apply, validate, summarize type defs.
            Replacement: VIBE_DOCUMENT_TYPES.md (section types and archetypes).

      - [ ] vibe/spec/VIBE_RUNTIME_HOOKS.md
            Reason: Runtime hooks are execution extensibility.
            Contains: Pre/post step hooks, gate hooks, custom event handlers.
            Replacement: VIBE_INTEGRATION_HOOKS.md (how external tools
            integrate with .vibe files, without execution semantics).

      - [ ] vibe/stdlib/schemas/plan_manifest.schema.json
            Reason: Plan manifest schema is a v1 execution artifact.
            Contains: JSON Schema for plan_manifest.json format.
            Replacement: None. No plan manifests in v2.

  - id: files_to_rewrite
    type: checklist
    title: "Files to REWRITE (11 files)"
    content: |
      These files have v2 equivalents but need substantial rewriting
      to reflect the document-oriented model.

      - [ ] project.vibe
            Current: v1 root program with tools, workflow, gates, retry.
            Target: v2 root document with meta (updated), imports (updated),
            context (updated). No workflow, no tools, no validation.
            Key changes: version bump, remove repo_write_scope, remove
            workflow section, update imports to v2 stdlib.

      - [ ] README.md
            Current: Describes VIBE as runtime execution format.
            Target: Describes VIBE as structured planning document format.
            Key changes: New tagline, updated feature list, MCP server
            setup instructions, updated example, new project structure.

      - [ ] vibe/spec/VIBE_SPEC_v1.md -> VIBE_SPEC_v2.md
            Current: v1 program format spec with tools, workflow, validation.
            Target: v2 document format spec with sections, decisions, quality.
            Key changes: All top-level fields redefined, program model
            replaced with document model, examples updated.

      - [ ] vibe/spec/VIBE_REFERENCE_PROGRAM.md -> VIBE_REFERENCE_DOCUMENT.md
            Current: Canonical v1 program with workflow steps and plan manifest.
            Target: Canonical v2 document showing sections, decisions, quality.
            Key changes: Replace execution example with planning document
            example. Show a realistic planning scenario.

      - [ ] vibe/spec/VIBE_AUTHORING_GUIDE.md
            Current: Guide for writing v1 programs (plan first, manifest, gates).
            Target: Guide for writing v2 documents (section types, decisions,
            quality criteria, using MCP server).
            Key changes: Replace "golden rules" with document-oriented guidance,
            update project layout, remove plan manifest references.

      - [ ] vibe/spec/VIBE_ERRORS.md
            Current: Runtime error taxonomy and codes.
            Target: Document validation error taxonomy (parse errors, schema
            errors, import resolution errors). No runtime errors.

      - [ ] vibe/spec/VIBE_SCOPE.md
            Current: Repository write scope rules and protected regions.
            Target: Remove or merge into spec. Write scope was a runtime
            concern. If kept, reframe as document scope guidance.

      - [ ] vibe/spec/VIBE_SUBAGENTS.md -> VIBE_MULTI_AUTHOR.md
            Current: Subagent delegation for multi-agent workflows.
            Target: Multi-author patterns for .vibe documents. How multiple
            AI systems or humans collaborate on planning documents.
            Key changes: Replace runtime delegation with document co-authoring
            patterns. Author tracking via meta.author field.

      - [ ] vibe/spec/VIBE_INDEX.md
            Current: Index of v1 spec documents.
            Target: Index of v2 spec documents with updated categories.

      - [ ] vibe/schema/vibe.schema.json
            Current: JSON Schema for v1 .vibe file format.
            Target: JSON Schema for v2 .vibe file format.
            Key changes: Remove tools, workflow, validation, legacy fields.
            Add sections, decisions, quality. Update meta fields.

      - [ ] vibe/templates/new_project.vibe
            Current: v1 project template with workflow and tools.
            Target: v2 document template with sections and quality.

  - id: files_to_adapt
    type: checklist
    title: "Files to ADAPT (4 files)"
    content: |
      These files need targeted changes but retain most of their
      current content.

      - [ ] vibe/stdlib/gates.vibe
            Change: Remove execution gate semantics, keep quality gate
            concepts. Merge useful content into new quality.vibe.
            Then delete this file.

      - [ ] vibe/stdlib/validators.vibe
            Change: Convert executable validators to quality criteria
            patterns. Merge useful content into new quality.vibe.
            Then delete this file.

      - [ ] vibe/stdlib/context_budget.vibe
            Change: Update to v2 format (vibe: 2.0). Remove references
            to runtime steps and plan manifests. Keep context window
            management guidance (still relevant for AI planning).

      - [ ] vibe/spec/VIBE_DEPENDENCIES.md
            Change: Update artifact dependency semantics for v2.
            Remove execution-time dependency resolution. Keep
            design-time dependency tracking between artifacts.

  - id: files_to_keep
    type: checklist
    title: "Files to KEEP (3 files)"
    content: |
      These files are format-agnostic and don't need changes.

      - [x] syntaxes/vibe.tmLanguage.json
            Reason: Syntax highlighting works for both v1 and v2 YAML.
            Note: May want to add highlighting for new keywords
            (sections, decisions, quality) but not required.

      - [x] .vscode/language-configuration.json
            Reason: VS Code language configuration is format-agnostic.

      - [x] package.json
            Reason: VS Code extension manifest is format-agnostic.
            Note: May update description text but structure unchanged.

  - id: new_spec_documents
    type: checklist
    title: "New Spec Documents to CREATE (5 files)"
    content: |
      These are new documents that replace deleted v1 spec docs
      with v2-oriented equivalents.

      - [ ] vibe/spec/VIBE_DOCUMENT_TYPES.md
            Replaces: VIBE_STEP_TYPES.md
            Contains: Section type definitions, document archetypes,
            quality criteria types. Based on 20_document_types.vibe.

      - [ ] vibe/spec/VIBE_CONSUMER_CONTRACT.md
            Replaces: VIBE_RUNTIME_CONTRACT.md
            Contains: What consumers (humans, AI, tools) need to know
            to correctly read and interpret .vibe documents. Parsing
            rules, merge behavior, field semantics.

      - [ ] vibe/spec/VIBE_MERGE_SEMANTICS.md
            Replaces: VIBE_PROGRAM_IR.md
            Contains: Simplified import resolution and field merge
            rules. Based on 10_format_spec.vibe import_merge section.

      - [ ] vibe/spec/VIBE_INTEGRATION_HOOKS.md
            Replaces: VIBE_RUNTIME_HOOKS.md
            Contains: How external tools integrate with .vibe files.
            MCP integration, IDE integration, CI/CD integration.

      - [ ] vibe/spec/VIBE_MCP_SERVER.md
            New document (no v1 equivalent).
            Contains: MCP server specification, tool reference, prompt
            reference, resource reference. Based on 40_mcp_server.vibe.

  - id: migration_order
    type: checklist
    title: Recommended Execution Order
    content: |
      Phase 1: Schema and stdlib (no spec doc dependencies)
        1. [ ] Update vibe/schema/vibe.schema.json to v2
        2. [ ] Create vibe/stdlib/quality.vibe
        3. [ ] Create vibe/stdlib/templates/ directory and templates
        4. [ ] Update vibe/stdlib/context_budget.vibe to v2

      Phase 2: Root files
        5. [ ] Rewrite project.vibe to v2
        6. [ ] Rewrite vibe/templates/new_project.vibe to v2

      Phase 3: Spec documents (can be parallelized)
        7. [ ] Create VIBE_SPEC_v2.md (rewrite of VIBE_SPEC_v1.md)
        8. [ ] Create VIBE_DOCUMENT_TYPES.md (new)
        9. [ ] Create VIBE_CONSUMER_CONTRACT.md (new)
        10. [ ] Create VIBE_MERGE_SEMANTICS.md (new)
        11. [ ] Create VIBE_INTEGRATION_HOOKS.md (new)
        12. [ ] Create VIBE_MCP_SERVER.md (new)
        13. [ ] Rewrite VIBE_REFERENCE_DOCUMENT.md
        14. [ ] Rewrite VIBE_AUTHORING_GUIDE.md
        15. [ ] Rewrite VIBE_ERRORS.md
        16. [ ] Rewrite VIBE_MULTI_AUTHOR.md
        17. [ ] Update VIBE_DEPENDENCIES.md
        18. [ ] Handle VIBE_SCOPE.md (merge or rewrite)
        19. [ ] Update VIBE_INDEX.md (last, references all others)

      Phase 4: Cleanup
        20. [ ] Delete vibe/stdlib/tools.vibe
        21. [ ] Delete vibe/stdlib/plan_manifest_schema.vibe
        22. [ ] Delete vibe/stdlib/schemas/plan_manifest.schema.json
        23. [ ] Delete vibe/stdlib/gates.vibe
        24. [ ] Delete vibe/stdlib/validators.vibe
        25. [ ] Delete VIBE_RUNTIME_CONTRACT.md
        26. [ ] Delete VIBE_PROGRAM_IR.md
        27. [ ] Delete VIBE_STEP_TYPES.md
        28. [ ] Delete VIBE_RUNTIME_HOOKS.md
        29. [ ] Delete VIBE_SPEC_v1.md (after v2 is in place)

      Phase 5: README and MCP server
        30. [ ] Rewrite README.md
        31. [ ] Build MCP server (separate implementation task)

decisions:
  - id: dec_single_branch
    title: Execute migration in a single branch
    status: proposed
    context: |
      Should the migration be executed incrementally across multiple
      PRs or in a single branch?
    options:
      - name: single_branch
        description: All changes in one branch, one PR
      - name: incremental
        description: Multiple PRs, each handling a phase
    chosen: single_branch
    rationale: |
      The changes are deeply interdependent. Incremental migration would
      leave the repo in an inconsistent state between PRs (half v1, half
      v2). A single branch keeps the transition atomic. Git history
      preserves the v1 state for rollback.
    consequences:
      - Large PR but atomic transition
      - No intermediate inconsistent states
      - Rollback is a single git revert

  - id: dec_delete_not_deprecate
    title: Delete v1-only files rather than deprecating
    status: proposed
    context: |
      Should v1-only files be deleted or kept with deprecation notices?
    options:
      - name: delete
        description: Remove files entirely, rely on git history
      - name: deprecate
        description: Keep files with deprecation headers pointing to v2 equivalents
    chosen: delete
    rationale: |
      Deprecated files create confusion about which version is current.
      Git history is the archive. Clean deletion makes the repo clearly
      v2-only after migration.
    consequences:
      - Clean repo with only v2 files
      - Git history required to access v1 content
      - No deprecation maintenance burden

quality:
  - id: q_complete_inventory
    type: checklist
    description: Every repository file is categorized
    criteria: |
      - All files in vibe/stdlib/ are accounted for
      - All files in vibe/spec/ are accounted for
      - All files in vibe/schema/ are accounted for
      - Root-level files (project.vibe, README.md) are accounted for
      - VS Code extension files are accounted for

  - id: q_no_orphans
    type: review
    description: No files reference deleted content
    criteria: |
      - After migration, no imports reference deleted files
      - No spec documents reference deleted spec docs without noting removal
      - README doesn't reference v1 concepts

  - id: q_executable_checklist
    type: review
    description: Migration can be executed as a checklist
    criteria: |
      - Each item is specific and actionable
      - Execution order handles dependencies
      - Each phase can be verified before moving to next
